        <div n="400-ROGP" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-400-ROGP-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-400-ROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-400-ROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"><hi rend="underline">I</hi></l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-400-ROGP-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-400-ROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-400-ROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-400-ROGP-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-400-ROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-400-ROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-400-ROGP-line-1"> The sage, who said he should be proud&#13;Of windows in his breast;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-400-ROGP-line-2"> Because he ne'er one thought allowedThat might not be confessed;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-400-ROGP-line-3"> His window scrawled by every rake,His breast again would cover;</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-400-ROGP-line-4"> And fairly bid the devil takeThe diamond and the lover.400-ROGP   </l></lg></div>
